      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHY SHOULD SHE (8) was out of the placings last time but before that was an impressive winner (21.90) in a Maiden at Broken Hill. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Likely to improve sharply this time. MASTER KILCOY (2) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish 0.8 lengths away in second (17.22) behind Aurora Sunshine at Murray Bridge. The form from his last run stacks up well. Will give a great sight again. TOMMY FIRE (4) recorded his 2nd career win last time at this track, scoring by 1.3 lengths (20.04). Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. SHE'S GOT DESIGN (1) was well fancied in betting last start but could only manage 2.25 lengths away in second (20.01). Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings five times from eight attempts. Ready to find winning form.",
